Every App requires top level main function where execution Starts

    Hello World :

    void main(){
        print("Hello");
    }


VARIABLES:

Variable Types are defined by initial Values.
But you can declare type Explicitly:

Type Safe Code:

    void main() {
        var firstName = 'Shashank';
        var lastName = 'Sharan';
        var age = 25;
        var heightInFeet = 5.7;
        var projects = [
            'Amdocs OMS',
            'BMC Helix Digital Workplace',
            'Citi Bank Online IIT'
        ];
        var vehicle = {'name': 'Honda Amaze', 'model': 'VX'};

        print('name' + firstName + ' ' + lastName);
        print('Age : ' + age.toString());
        print('Height : ' + heightInFeet.toString() + ' Feet');
        print("Projects : " + projects.toString());
        print("Vehicle : " + vehicle.toString());
    }

IMPORTS:

    // Importing core libraries
    import 'dart:math';

    // Importing libraries from external packages
    import 'package:test/test.dart';

    // Importing files
    import 'path/to/my_other_file.dart';